  "title": "Audit Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Highlights</strong></p><p>·   Training and development opportunities<br />·    Performance-based bonus<br />·     Open door policy and positive work culture</p><p><strong>Audit Manager</strong></p><p>Responsibilities</p><p>·   Plan, lead and serve a diversified local and international client base</p><p>·   Review of statutory financial statements in accordance with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards</p><p>·   Internal audit, special projects, transaction services and due diligence work</p><p>·    Provide on the job training and guidance to seniors and associates</p><p>Requirements:</p><p>·    Possess a Bachelor’s degree with major in accounting, or professional qualification such as ACCA, ICAEW, CPA Australia</p><p>·     Minimum 5 to 7 years’ work experience in audit</p><p>·     Ability to handle a portfolio of clients across industries, and planning, leading and managing the audit    assignments<br /></p><p><strong>Special Skill</strong><br /></p><p>·     Candidates should possess good command of English with excellent written and verbal communication skills, as well as interpersonal skills.</p><p>·     Candidates must also be prepared to work in a multi-cultural environment and travel, particularly to Asian countries.</p><p>·     Proficiency in an additional Asian Language is highly desired.<br /><br />·     Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Word and Excel is required.</p>",
